  <article class="prose-tool space-y-7">
    <h1>How to Reduce PDF Size Under 500KB</h1>
    <p>
      Many portals reject PDFs larger than 500KB or 1MB. The best method depends on whether your PDF is
      text-based, image-heavy or scanned from photos.
    </p>
    <h2>What works best</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>For text PDFs, structural optimization can reduce size without visible quality loss.</li>
      <li>For scanned PDFs, compress the images before converting them to PDF.</li>
      <li>Remove duplicate pages or blank pages before upload.</li>
      <li>Use black-and-white scanning for simple documents when color is not required.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Suggested workflow</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Compress images first using <a href="/tools/image-compress/">Image Compress</a>.</li>
      <li>Create the PDF using <a href="/tools/jpg-to-pdf/">JPG to PDF</a>.</li>
      <li>Try <a href="/tools/pdf-compressor/">PDF Compressor</a> for final optimization.</li>
    </ol>
  </article>
